    fix(render): M-RENDER-API Round-2 Codex fixes (DEC-V61-095)
    
    Codex Round 1 returned CHANGES_REQUIRED with 6 findings (2 P1 + 4 P2);
    this commit lands all 6 with regression tests.
    
    Finding 1 [P1] · source-path containment guard (symlink escape)
    - Each render service now resolve(strict=True)'s the chosen source file
      and asserts it stays under the case dir before reading. Previously
      is_safe_case_id + segment validators caught literal traversal in URL
      path segments but a symlink under triSurface/, constant/polyMesh/, or
      <run_id>/<name> could redirect us outside IMPORTED_DIR.
    - Affected: geometry_glb._resolve_source_stl, mesh_wireframe._polymesh_source_files,
      field_sample._resolve_field_path
    - Tests: 3 new symlink-escape regression tests
    
    Finding 2 [P1] · field-sample dead-code fallback removed
    - field_sample.py probed reports/phase5_fields/{case_id}/{run_id}/{name}
      as a "completed run" fallback but the actual phase5 layout is
      {case_id}/{timestamp}/VTK/... — that path could never resolve a real
      archived run. Tier-A scope per spec_v2 §B.3 is the imported case dir
      only; the fallback was Codex round-1 dead code.
    - Tier-A scope unchanged (M-VIZ.results upgrades to baked glTF colors
      for archived runs).
    
    Finding 3 [P2] · cache-write race (TOCTOU on mtime)
    - All three render services now snapshot st_mtime_ns before transcode
      and re-stat after. If the source mutates during the build window, the
      service raises rather than os.replace'ing a stale-but-fresh-mtimed
      payload over a newer cache. Next request rebuilds against the newer
      source.
    
    Finding 4 [P2] · polyMesh face-index bounds validation
    - New polymesh_parser.validate_face_indices(faces, n_points) rejects
      faces referencing vertex IDs outside [0, n_points). Previously a face
      like 4(0 1 2 999) (with 8 points) survived parse_faces (only arity
      was checked) and produced a glTF indices accessor pointing past the
      POSITION buffer. Called from mesh_wireframe._build_wireframe_bytes
      between parse and edge extraction.
    - Tests: 3 new (in-range pass / OOB reject / negative reject) +
      end-to-end test_build_mesh_wireframe_422_on_face_index_out_of_range.
    
    Finding 5 [P2] · GLB importer ownership on attachGltf throw
    - viewport_kernel.attachGltf now wraps setRenderer + importActors in
      try/catch, deletes the importer and re-raises on failure, and only
      transfers ownership (assigns to module-level `importer` var) AFTER
      importActors() succeeds. Previously a half-imported reference would
      leak until the next dispose.
    - Test: new "renders an error banner when kernel.attachGltf throws" +
      "disposes the kernel on unmount even on the glb path".
    
    Finding 6 [P2] · GLTFImporter eagerly bundled
    - glb_loader now uses dynamic `await import("@kitware/.../GLTFImporter")`
      inside parseGlbBytes; only a `import type` reference remains at the
      top level for the GlbData interface. Vite splits GLTFImporter into a
      separate chunk:
        - Before: Viewport chunk = 722.81 KB / 201.85 KB gz
        - After:  Viewport chunk = 689.70 KB / 191.58 KB gz
                  GLTFImporter chunk = 34.10 KB / 11.29 KB gz (lazy)
      STL-only Viewport consumers save 11.29 KB gz; spec_v2 §AC#10 +50 KB
      delta budget preserved with margin.
    - parseGlbBytes is now async (was sync). Only caller (loadGlbFromUrl)
      was already inside an async function so no observable behavior change.
      Test updated to await both parseGlbBytes paths.
    
    Verification:
    - backend: 57/57 pass (was 50 → +7 regression tests for Findings 1+4)
    - frontend typecheck: clean
    - frontend tests: 41/41 pass (was 39 → +2 for Finding 5)
    - frontend build: GLTFImporter chunk-split confirmed in bundle output
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

