    - New polymesh_parser.validate_face_indices(faces, n_points) rejects
      faces referencing vertex IDs outside [0, n_points). Previously a face
      like 4(0 1 2 999) (with 8 points) survived parse_faces (only arity
      was checked) and produced a glTF indices accessor pointing past the
      POSITION buffer. Called from mesh_wireframe._build_wireframe_bytes
      between parse and edge extraction.
    - Tests: 3 new (in-range pass / OOB reject / negative reject) +
      end-to-end test_build_mesh_wireframe_422_on_face_index_out_of_range.
    
